sql:
SELECT roles.role_name, security.permission_type
FROM roles
INNER JOIN security ON roles.role_id = security.role_id;

external_knowledge:
- Financial period refers to the current year and quarter;
- Total annual rewards include base salary, benefits, bonus, variable pay, and stock options;
- Staff identities are represented by employee names and IDs;
- Department corresponds to cost center.

- "top overworkers" refers to those who have worked more overtime than the company average;
- "extra time" corresponds to the actual number of overtime hours worked by each individual;
- "average employee" is defined by the average overtime hours across all employees.

sql:
SELECT E.employee_name, M.manager_name
FROM employees E
INNER JOIN managers M ON E.region_id = M.region_id;
